The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 London, April 17 (PTI): The producers of Slumdog Millionaire have set up a 500,000 (Rs 3.7 crore) fund for health and education programmes for poor children in Mumbai.           
	The money will be administered by an international childrens charity. The filmmakers also have formed a trust to look after the two child actors in the movie.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The brother of Sajjan Kumar, widely accused in the Sikh riots, has been nominated from the South Delhi seat. Sajjan had to withdraw his nomination in the wake of protests by Sikhs against CBIs clean chit to him and Jagdish Tytler.                  
	 Rajkot (PTI): A boy was allegedly beaten up severely by two teachers who suspected him of stealing money. Rahul Rathod, the Class V student, has been hospitalised. He was allegedly beaten after one of the teachers found Rs 15 missing from his purse.                   
	 Kannur (PTI): Two persons, including the son of CPM MLA P. Jayarajan, were injured when the crackers they were carrying went off accidentally. Ashish P. Raj, 22, the MLAs son had bought the crackers to celebrate Vishu, the new year festival of Kerala.                                                                                                                           
